-- China Positions for Foreign Exchange Purchases Fall 54% in May From April
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-22T00:03:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/china-positions-for-foreign-exchange-purchases-falls-54-in-may-from-april.html

          
          
             China’s position for foreign
exchange purchases fell 54 percent in May from the month before
to 131.6 billion yuan ($19 billion), according to a statement on
the website of the People’s Bank of China.  
 This was the lowest level since August, the Shanghai
Securities News reported today, citing the data.  
